Landslides and power outages occurred in the epicentral area. Felt (VIII) at Arica, Codpa and Cuya; (VII) at Alto Hospicio and Iquique. Felt from Arequipa, Peru east to Cochabamba, Bolivia and south to Santiago, Chile. The tsunami had maximum runup heights of 2.12 m at Pisagua, 2.01 m at Arica, 1.80 m at Iquique and 1.66 m at Patache. Tsunami wave heights (in cm above sea level) were recorded at the following selected tide gauges:  20 at Esperance and 7 at Port Kembla, Australia; 87 at Tocopilla, 45 at Chanaral, 36 at Talcahuano and 33 at Coquimbo, Chile; 57 on Isla Santa Cruz, Ecuador; 55 on Hiva Oa, French Polynesia; 19 at Kushimoto, Japan; 16 at Salina Cruz, Mexico; 12 at Ouinne, New Caledonia; 30 at Waitangi and 19 at Gisborne, New Zealand; 58 at Matarani, Peru; 12 at Apia, Samoa; 6 at Lata Wharf, Solomon Islands; 7 at Nuku`alofa, Tonga; 10 at King Cove, Alaska; 22 at Port San Luis, California; 57 at Hilo and 53 at Kahului, Hawaii; 35 at Pago Pago, American Samoa. </text></comment><focalMechanism publicID="quakeml:us.anss.org/focalmechanism/c000nzvd/mwc" catalog:datasource="us"
